诺顿
Norton!

02:03:45.660 --> 02:03:48.330
别自找麻烦  诺顿
Make it easy on yourself, Norton.

02:03:59.580 --> 02:04:03.040
我猜他脑中最后一件事
I like to think the last thing that went through his head,

02:04:03.250 --> 02:04:04.840
除了枪子儿
other than that bullet,

02:04:05.050 --> 02:04:09.490
就是在想安迪为何能整倒他
was to wonder how the hell Andy Dufresne ever got the best of him.

02:04:10.290 --> 02:04:11.880
詹姆斯·卡特
Carter, James...

02:04:11.990 --> 02:04:15.450
典狱长呜呼后不久
Not long after the Warden deprived us of his company,

02:04:15.730 --> 02:04:17.790
我收到一张明信片
I got a postcard in the mail.

02:04:19.260 --> 02:04:22.100
没写字  但有邮戳
It was blank, but the postmark said...

02:04:22.300 --> 02:04:24.430
来自德州汉考克堡
Fort Hancock, Texas.

02:04:24.970 --> 02:04:26.330
汉考克堡
Fort Hancock.

02:04:26.600 --> 02:04:28.330
就在边境线上
Right on the border.

02:04:28.740 --> 02:04:30.730
安迪就是从那里出境的
That's where Andy crossed.

02:04:31.310 --> 02:04:35.440
驾着敞蓬车驶向南方
When I picture him heading south in his own car with the top down,

02:04:35.780 --> 02:04:38.010
想到这画面就令我开怀大笑
it always makes me laugh.

02:04:39.850 --> 02:04:41.410
安迪·杜弗伦
Andy Dufresne,

02:04:41.790 --> 02:04:43.810
爬过肮脏的下水道
who crawled through a river of shit...

02:04:44.020 --> 02:04:46.420
出来已焕然一新
and came out clean on the other side.

02:04:47.260 --> 02:04:48.620
安迪·杜弗伦
Andy Dufresne,

02:04:49.430 --> 02:04:51.020
向太平洋驶去
headed for the Pacific.

02:04:54.000 --> 02:04:56.160
海利掐住他喉咙说
Hadley's got him by the toes, right?

02:04:56.370 --> 02:05:00.170
“他活的不耐烦了。”
And he says, "I believe this boy's about to have himself an accident."

02:05:00.370 --> 02:05:03.240
老友们常聊起他
Those of us who knew him best talk about him often.

02:05:03.910 --> 02:05:05.600
他那些惊人之举
I swear, the stuff he pulled...

02:05:05.810 --> 02:05:08.300
“请我朋友喝啤酒吧……”
"These friends of mine could use a couple of beers!"

02:05:08.300 --> 02:05:10.770
-他真的做到了！ -真就做到了！
-And he got it. -And he got it!

02:05:12.020 --> 02:05:14.420
有时我会感伤
Sometimes it makes me sad, though,

02:05:14.690 --> 02:05:16.120
他的离去
Andy being gone.

02:05:16.820 --> 02:05:18.020
我不得不提醒自己
I have to remind myself that...

02:05:18.020 --> 02:05:19.950
有些鸟儿是关不住的
some birds aren't meant to be caged.

02:05:21.430 --> 02:05:23.490
它们的羽毛太鲜亮了
Their feathers are just too bright.

02:05:25.200 --> 02:05:26.930
当它们飞离时
And when they fly away,

02:05:27.370 --> 02:05:31.770
你会由衷欣慰它们重获自由
the part of you that knows it was a sin to lock them up does rejoice.

02:05:32.840 --> 02:05:34.100
无奈的是
But still...

02:05:34.570 --> 02:05:38.910
你得继续在这乏味之地苟活
the place you live in is that much more drab and empty that they're gone.

02:05:43.110 --> 02:05:45.480
这么说或许出于我对这位友伴的怀念
I guess I just miss my friend.

02:06:09.940 --> 02:06:11.100
请坐
Please sit down.

02:06:16.950 --> 02:06:18.510
埃利斯·博伊德·瑞丁
Ellis Boyd Redding.

02:06:19.050 --> 02:06:22.320
根据你的材料 你的终身监禁已经服满40年
Your files say you've served 40 years of a life sentence.

02:06:23.120 --> 02:06:25.250
你改过自新了吗？
Do you feel you've been rehabilitated?

02:06:27.130 --> 02:06:28.680
改过自新？
Rehabilitated?

02:06:30.730 --> 02:06:32.630
噢  让我想想
Well, now, let me see.

02:06:33.630 --> 02:06:35.960
我不大明白这个词的含义
You know, I don't have any idea what that means.

02:06:38.070 --> 02:06:40.330
就是说准备好重返社会
Well, it means you're ready to rejoin society...

02:06:40.910 --> 02:06:43.240
我当然明白你的意思  年轻人
I know what you think it means, sonny.

02:06:45.410 --> 02:06:47.400
对我而言  这只是个虚词
To me, it's just a made-up word.

02:06:48.750 --> 02:06:51.080
政客发明的词
A politician's word so that...

02:06:51.520 --> 02:06:55.040
好让你们穿西装打领带
young fellas like yourself can wear a suit and a tie...

02:06:55.520 --> 02:06:57.110
有活干
and have a job.

02:06:59.090 --> 02:07:01.180
你到底想了解什么？
What do you really want to know?

02:07:01.960 --> 02:07:03.930
我后悔犯罪吗？
Am I sorry for what I did?

02:07:04.360 --> 02:07:05.520
你后悔吗？
Well, are you?

02:07:07.430 --> 02:07:10.270
我没有一天不后悔
There's not a day goes by I don't feel regret.

02:07:11.640 --> 02:07:15.090
但并非因为关在这里  也不为讨好你们
Not because I'm in here or because you think I should.

02:07:18.580 --> 02:07:21.140
回首前尘往事
I look back on the way I was then.

02:07:23.280 --> 02:07:24.440
那个
A young...

02:07:25.550 --> 02:07:29.040
犯下重罪的小笨蛋
stupid kid who committed that terrible crime.

02:07:32.060 --> 02:07:33.750
我想跟他谈谈
I want to talk to him.

02:07:35.690 --> 02:07:38.180
想给他讲一些感受
I wanna try and talk some sense to him,

02:07:38.900 --> 02:07:40.830
给他讲冲动酿下的苦果
tell him the way things are.

02:07:42.930 --> 02:07:44.370
但我办不到
But I can't.

02:07:46.570 --> 02:07:48.560
那个少年早就不见了
That kid's long gone.

02:07:49.770 --> 02:07:52.540
只剩下我垂老之躯
This old man is all that's left.

02:07:53.950 --> 02:07:55.440
我得接受事实
I gotta live with that.

02:07:56.780 --> 02:07:58.480
改过自新？
Rehabilitated?

02:07:58.850 --> 02:08:00.680
狗屁不通的词儿
It's just a bullshit word.

02:08:01.620 --> 02:08:06.390
盖章吧  别浪费我的时间
So you go on and stamp your form, sonny, and stop wasting my time.

02:08:07.630 --> 02:08:09.890
跟你说句实话吧
Because to tell you the truth,

02:08:10.230 --> 02:08:12.220
我他妈的不在乎了
I don't give a shit.

02:08:25.020 --> 02:08:26.800
批      准

02:09:21.330 --> 02:09:26.060
老布
到此一游

02:09:38.750 --> 02:09:40.150
你的  小姐
Here you go, miss.

02:09:43.090 --> 02:09:44.110
可以上厕所吗？
Rest room break, boss?

02:09:49.930 --> 02:09:54.460
别一小解就来报告  要去就去  懂吗?
You don't need to ask me every time you need to go take a piss. Just go. Understand?

02:09:55.500 --> 02:09:57.090
是
Yes, sir.

02:10:07.510 --> 02:10:10.570
我报告了40年
40 years I've been asking permission to piss.

02:10:11.420 --> 02:10:14.410
不报告  一滴也挤不出
I can't squeeze a drop without say-so.

02:10:17.920 --> 02:10:20.080
我得面对一个残酷的事实
There's a harsh truth to face.

02:10:21.760 --> 02:10:24.660
在狱外我根本混不下去
No way I'm gonna make it on the outside.

02:10:32.540 --> 02:10:36.230
我一心想违犯假释
All I do any more is think of ways to break my parole...

02:10:37.040 --> 02:10:39.530
也许就能重返肖申克
so maybe they'd send me back.

02:10:44.720 --> 02:10:47.150
活在恐惧中真是糟糕
A terrible thing to live in fear.

02:10:48.050 --> 02:10:49.710
老布体会过
Brooks Hatlen knew it,

02:10:49.920 --> 02:10:51.860
他看透了
knew it all too well.

02:10:53.460 --> 02:10:56.860
我只想回到有意义的地方
All I want is to be back where things make sense,

02:10:57.300 --> 02:11:00.030
不必整天担惊受怕
where I won't have to be afraid all the time.

02:11:02.030 --> 02:11:04.400
只有一件事阻止了我
Only one thing stops me.

02:11:05.840 --> 02:11:08.240
我向安迪做过承诺
A promise I made to Andy.

02:11:28.760 --> 02:11:29.890
到了
There it is.

02:11:40.500 --> 02:11:42.170
非常感谢您
Much obliged, sir.

02:11:48.520 --> 02:11:50.200
巴克斯顿

02:11:50.990 --> 02:11:53.560
巴克斯顿

02:11:53.560 --> 02:11:57.580
巴克斯顿

02:15:21.490 --> 02:15:22.750
“亲爱的瑞德：”
Dear Red,

02:15:22.990 --> 02:15:25.480
“见到这封信的时候，你已经出狱了。”
If you're reading this, you've gotten out.

02:15:25.660 --> 02:15:29.720
“既然走了这么远的路，干脆再走远一点吧。”
And if you've come this far, maybe you're willing to come a little further.

02:15:30.000 --> 02:15:32.490
“你还记得那个地方的名字，是吗？”
You remember the name of the town, don't you?

02:15:34.770 --> 02:15:36.260
芝华塔尼欧
Zihuatanejo.

02:15:37.910 --> 02:15:41.500
“请来帮我实现计划，”
I could use a good man to help me get my project on wheels.

02:15:42.010 --> 02:15:45.540
“我备妥棋盘等着你。”
I'll keep an eye out for you, and the chessboard ready.

02:15:46.350 --> 02:15:47.750
“记住，瑞德，”
Remember, Red,

02:15:48.090 --> 02:15:50.180
“希望是美好的，”
hope is a good thing,

02:15:50.390 --> 02:15:52.380
“也许是最好的，”
maybe the best of things,

02:15:52.590 --> 02:15:54.750
“而美好之物，永不消逝。”
and no good thing ever dies.

02:15:55.290 --> 02:15:58.160
“希望这封信，能让我再次见到你，”
I will be hoping that this letter finds you...

02:15:58.360 --> 02:16:00.090
“一个健在的你。”
and finds you well.

02:16:00.600 --> 02:16:01.830
“你的朋友，”
Your friend,

02:16:02.030 --> 02:16:03.190
“安迪”
Andy.

02:16:37.030 --> 02:16:38.760
“要么忙着活，”
"Get busy living...

02:16:38.970 --> 02:16:40.870
“要么忙着死。”
or get busy dying."

02:16:43.570 --> 02:16:45.740
这话真他妈的精辟
That's goddamn right.

02:16:46.090 --> 02:16:50.050
也来过

02:16:46.100 --> 02:16:50.040
瑞德

02:16:50.040 --> 02:16:53.000
瑞德

02:16:50.050 --> 02:16:52.980
也来过

02:16:50.980 --> 02:16:53.110
这是生平第二次
For the second time in my life,

02:16:53.350 --> 02:16:55.910
我又犯了罪
I'm guilty of committing a crime.

02:16:56.990 --> 02:16:58.920
违反假释出城
Parole violation.

02:16:59.590 --> 02:17:03.250
我怀疑警方会设路障抓我
Of course, I doubt they'll toss up any roadblocks for that.

02:17:03.930 --> 02:17:05.950
不过我这种老贼大可免了
Not for an old crook like me.

02:17:06.160 --> 02:17:08.190
去德州汉考克堡  谢谢
Fort Hancock, Texas, please.

02:17:11.870 --> 02:17:16.600
我激动得不能安坐或思考
I find I'm so excited I can barely sit still or hold a thought in my head.

02:17:17.040 --> 02:17:20.370
我想  只有真正的自由人
I think it's the excitement only a free man can feel.

02:17:20.580 --> 02:17:23.070
在踏上远征那一刻  才会生出这种
A free man at the start of a long journey...

02:17:23.280 --> 02:17:25.870
即将揭开未来神秘面纱的激动心情吧
whose conclusion is uncertain.

02:17:28.890 --> 02:17:31.550
我希望能顺利跨越边境
I hope I can make it across the border.

02:17:33.060 --> 02:17:36.080
我希望能跟重逢老友握握手
I hope to see my friend and shake his hand.

02:17:37.960 --> 02:17:42.020
我希望太平洋如梦中一般蓝
I hope the Pacific is as blue as it has been in my dreams.

02:17:43.870 --> 02:17:45.060
我满怀希望
I hope.

02:18:18.670 --> 02:18:24.460
谨此纪念艾伦·格林

02:18:19.670 --> 02:18:26.460
此处字幕是导演献给他的经纪人艾伦·格林，
他在电影完成前因艾滋病并发症去世.